<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="abcb-glossentry" ?><abcb-glossentry xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_b74613d6-3cf2-489a-af62-321caa6c43d5" outputclass="abcb-glossentry"><glossterm id="_4ad91513-1fc5-4dd0-b560-9e491d77dedd">Occupiable outdoor area</glossterm><glossdef outputclass="glossdef"><p>A space on a roof, balcony or similar part of a building—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_cf091876-d2c1-498e-9765-2db4349b5dfd">that is open to the sky; and</li><li id="_7647b160-7794-4303-b79e-ac1a58aa1291">to which access is provided, other than access only for maintenance; and</li><li id="_87d39c22-afae-474d-a77a-ccf47668cd86">that is not <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1385_0.4.0.xml#_b4a20ca6-0197-4381-9e50-85c757fa574f" id="_ccea6259-3e64-44e0-9f11-33206b90ca99" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">open space</xref> or directly connected with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1385_0.4.0.xml#_b4a20ca6-0197-4381-9e50-85c757fa574f" id="_b3e04d69-75bb-4f4c-b7d1-86bc0ca3b0ed" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">open space</xref>.</li></ol><callout id="_dcff5b02-595c-4e76-8c92-246bbc46bbce"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>For the purposes of this definition, a minor roof covering that is open sided, such as an awning provided at a doorway, does not prevent an area from being considered ‘open to the sky’.</p></callout></glossdef></abcb-glossentry>